<p>Naturally Les Burnett the empty must nudge me at the Spiritualistic reference.</p>
<p>After dinner I had a sudden desire for a long walk in the beautiful Somme valley precincts. They are not really beautiful, for all this country has been fought over, &amp; bears unmistakeable signs of war, such as signal wires to trip one up at every few yards; pontoon bridges across the canal; dug-outs everywhere; heaps of ammunition for guns at unexpected places, &amp; rubbish in odd corners. Still the summer <strike>spring</strike> mantle of nature is only sullied by such things, &amp; when seen from an eminence loses not very much of its beauty. The Somme splits up into many branches here, some of them having become mere lagoons, so the canal was evidently</p>
